      "text": "Indexed\nfolder 90 - 179\nG 123\n\nIt's okay to believe because I know; I saw. I passed over to the other side. I recreated the past (in 2-74); I drew it back: {illustration: two boxes linked to one common box, probably symbolizing the meta-abstraction} - I broke the power of time in favor of meaning. I broke world, the power of delusion. It's all true; it has to do with organization in God's mind: the true ordering of reality. I have the key. I don't know it; I did it (2-3-74). It is Plato's anamne",
